Acer, Arima Communications: Taiwan Stocks Preview

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-09-20T01:43:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/acer-compal-communications-tsmc-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
(Corrects spelling of brokerage name in third paragraph,
company name in fourth.)  Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the last close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 96.52 points, or 1.3 percent, to
7,480.88.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT): The world’s fourth largest computer
maker had its share-price estimate cut 30 percent to NT$28 at
Sanford C. Bernstein & Co., which said the company’s low-price
strategy won’t drive volume growth and costs will crimp
profitability over next six to 12 months. The brokerage kept its
rating on Acer at “underperform.” The stock dropped 4.9
percent to NT$34.  Arima Communications Corp. (8101)  (8101 TT): The phone maker
raised its smartphone shipment target to 7 million for 2012,
Apple Daily reported today, without saying where it got the
information. The newspaper didn’t say what the previous target
was. The stock gained 1.6 percent to NT$18.80.  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (2330 TT): The
world’s largest contract maker of chips plans to lower  capital
spending  by 19 percent to $6 billion in 2012, from $7.4 billion
budgeted this year, the Taipei-based Commercial Times reported
today, without saying where it got the information. The stock
advanced 0.1 percent to NT$71.20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
